  <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website.
    They help websites remember your preferences and improve your experience.
  </p>

  <h2>How We Use Cookies</h2>
  <p>MyWebClass.org uses cookies for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for the website to function (e.g., remembering your cookie consent choice)</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors use our site (only loaded after consent)</li>
    <li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> Monitor site performance and identify issues</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookie Consent</h2>
  <p>
    We will not load any non-essential cookies (like analytics) until you
    explicitly consent through our cookie banner. You can change your
    preferences at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

  <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
  <p>These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be disabled:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>cookie_consent</code> - Stores your cookie preference choice</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Analytics Cookies (Optional)</h3>
  <p>With your consent, we use analytics to understand site usage:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Page views and navigation patterns</li>
    <li>Time spent on pages</li>
    <li>Device and browser information</li>
    <li>Referral sources</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We use privacy-focused analytics that do not track individual users
    across websites or collect personal information.
  </p>

  <h2>Managing Cookies</h2>
  <p>You can control cookies in several ways:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the cookie banner on first visit to accept or reject</li>
    <li>Change your preferences at any time (button in footer)</li>
    <li>Configure your browser to block or delete cookies</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third-Party Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    We do not allow third-party advertising cookies on our site. Analytics
    cookies are only used to improve our service and are GDPR-compliant.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Rights</h2>
  <p>
    Under GDPR and similar privacy laws, you have the right to withdraw
    cookie consent at any time without affecting the lawfulness of processing
    based on consent before its withdrawal.
  </p>

